Explain why this Go code can unexpectedly modify the original slice, and how append's backing-array sharing causes it:

```go
func main() {
	a := []int{1, 2, 3, 4, 5}
	b := a[:3]
	b = append(b, 99)
	fmt.Println(a)
}
```

