Explain how defer, panic, and recover interact in this Go code, and what it prints:

```go
func safeDivide(a, b int) (result int, err error) {
	defer func() {
		if r := recover(); r != nil {
			err = fmt.Errorf("recovered: %v", r)
		}
	}()
	return a / b, nil
}
```

