Explain how interfaces and implicit satisfaction work in this Go code, and why Rectangle doesn't need to declare that it implements Stringer:

```go
type Stringer interface{ String() string }

type Rectangle struct{ W, H int }

func (r Rectangle) String() string {
	return fmt.Sprintf("%dx%d", r.W, r.H)
}

func printIt(s Stringer) { fmt.Println(s.String()) }
```

